Caption included with image: Caterpillar tractors used by WPA in clearing the Grand Coulee reservoir are shown lined up for service beside the old Highway # 22 on the flat midway between the towns of Daisy and Rice, during final clearing operations in the Camp Gifford area. Lake water formed by the Columbia River backing up behind Grand Coulee dam will soon cover this area.

Caption on verso: US WPA 660

PH Coll 478.153
